title: Acne Studios’ New Ankle Boots Are Like Timberland Meets High Fashion
text:
Visit the original post to see all 4 images from this gallery. 
During the cooler months, a crisp pair of Timberlands is basically a must. But if you’re looking for a high fashion variant, then you may want to try Acne Studios .
The brand has recently released a pair of new boot silhouettes in the Telde and the Ugo. The Telde comes optioned in beige and black, as well as pink and black, featuring a puffy upper and seasonal tractor sole in rubber. Nubuck and patent leather then come together on the ankle boot, which also notes a six-eye lacing system.
The Ugo, on the other hand, arrives in khaki green and all-black, constructed from calf leather and cotton. The lace-up footwear then welcomes a padded back and rubber tractor sole.
You can purchase the Telde from Acne Studios today for $650 USD, as well as the Ugo for the same price.
